title: 2020 United States presidential election in Mississippi
added: Mississippi hasn't supported a Democrat for President since 1976. It is in the [[Deep South]] and overlapping [[Bible Belt]] regions, and, as is the case with its neighbouring states, most of its population is conservative on issues like [[gay rights]] and [[abortion rights]]; Therefore, it is a much easier target for the [[GOP]].
